gomodel:SYNGO_5458  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: RapGEF2 (aka; PDZ-GEF1, nRap-GEP, CNrasGEF, RA-GEF) is a neural-specific activator for both mammalian Rap proteins Rap1 and Rap2 (PMID:10608883).\n\nFigure 5: reverse IPs showed RapGEF2 interacts with PSD-Zip70 (LZTS1). In cultured neurons, both proteins co-localized at dendritic puncta. PSD-Zip70 also interacted and co-localized with SPAR (SIPA1L1), which is known to be localized to the postsynaptic density (PMID:11502259).\n\nFigure 6: PSD-Zip70 modulates Rap2 activity via SPAR and RapGEF2 in cultured neurons.\n\"Thus, the Rap2-specific activation in PSD-Zip70KO neurons may be related to the spatial association of PSD-Zip70 with SPAR and PDZ-GEF1 as a ternary complex close to Rap2 in the postsynapse.\"\n\nFigure 7: \"We then investigated the effect of Rap2 activity on the spine morphology in WT and PSD-Zip70KO neurons. The forced expression of PDZ-GEF1 or PDZ-GEF2 reduced the size of the spine head and altered the spine shape from mushroom to thin in WT neurons (Fig. 7a-c).\". Experimental description: M&M: \"Cultured neurons were prepared from mouse embryonic brain on embryonic day 16.5 (E16.5)\"\n\nantibody:\nanti-PDZ-GEF1 (H00009693) from Abnova" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2023-03-17" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5458" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

